News24 Correspondent iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Musina - A 43-year-old Limpopo man was shot and killed in Musina on Monday evening, police said on Tuesday.Police said the well-known businessman was gunned down on Monday night by two unknown suspects.His identity has not yet been released.Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said the deceased was apparently with a woman when the suspects, who spoke Shona, approached him and shot him dead.Mojapelo said the woman was not injured.The incident happened in Musina Extension 12. The man's pistol, cellphone and a friend's cellphone were taken by the suspects.Anyone with information was requested to contact their nearest police station.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.